UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=8956 SET `male_text`='Welcome to the Explorer\'s League.  If you need information, and it is in book form, then I might be able to help you out.', `female_text`='';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=8957 SET `male_text`='How can I find the two parts of your scepter?', `female_text`='How can I find the two parts of your scepter?';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=8958 SET `male_text`='As the toxins lurking within Maraudon seeped into my mind, I began to lose my grip on reality. Worried that it would be used for evil, my dryad sisters secretly took the scepter from me, breaking it into two parts and hiding it within the caverns.$B$BSoon they fell victim to the madness as well, and the two parts of the scepter, left unguarded, came to be in the possession of Vyletongue, himself. The satyr entrusted one part to Noxxion, an evil elemental, and the other he still has to this day.', `female_text`='';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=8959 SET `male_text`='Why didn\'t Lord Vyletongue unite both parts of the scepter into one?', `female_text`='Why didn\'t Lord Vyletongue unite both parts of the scepter into one?';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=8960 SET `male_text`='Without knowledge of the incantations required to unite the two parts, Lord Vyletongue was unable to use the scepter. However, now that I am free of the curse of Vyletongue\'s corruption, I will be able to assist you, if you\'d like to bring me the two parts -- both the head and the rod of the scepter.', `female_text`='';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=8961 SET `male_text`='Tell me more about the history of Remulos and Zaetar.', `female_text`='Tell me more about the history of Remulos and Zaetar.';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=8962 SET `male_text`='You ask of the Sons of Cenarius, Remulos and Zaetar.$B$BMy father, Remulos, was strong and beautiful, and my uncle, Zaetar, very cunning and slight of build. While they were respected quite equally, Zaetar always felt as if he could never quite compare to the glory and attention he thought Remulos had.$B$BAfter my sisters and I were born, Zaetar, blinded by jealousy, set out to outdo his brother... He was the creator of his own end. The sadness it brings me has never lessened, even as time passes...', `female_text`='';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=8963 SET `male_text`='Long have my spirit and remains been kept captive here within Maraudon, young $c. The time has given me nothing but ample opportunities to reflect on my mistakes and realize that my jealousy of Remulos was foolish. He attempted to warn and persuade me that my relations with Theradras would bear nothing pure--that only destruction would come from chaos. My brother was right.$B$BBut that does not mean since you have freed me, I am free of penance.', `female_text`='';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=8964 SET `male_text`='Please, go on.', `female_text`='Please, go on.';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=8965 SET `male_text`='Though exiled as a heretic, my beliefs still ring true--that alone drives me onward. But for my destiny to be complete, I need the aid of an outsider... one not of any centaur tribe.$B$BThe task requires someone to enter the holy halls of Maraudon--a temple my people protect, and only the most devout are ever allowed to enter.$B$BIf you agree to aid me, then you need only nod. I will pass you a parchment with my instructions on it. Read it over and consider my words.', `female_text`='';
