UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=11916 SET `male_text`='It\'s quite simple, really, $n. My old merc company, The Veiled Blade, took the wrong mission at the wrong time.$B$BWe were hired by a goblin smuggler out of Booty Bay, one Gremnik Rizzlesprang, who was covetous of Lord Valthalak\'s spellbook. Or, maybe there was some old rivalry there? I suppose we\'ll never know now, because Gremnik was killed not too long ago by a group of Valthalak\'s spectral assassins. They really can be very deadly when a large number of them gather.$B$BWhere was I?', `female_text`='';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=11917 SET `male_text`='You were telling me about The Veiled Blade and how you took the wrong mission.', `female_text`='You were telling me about The Veiled Blade and how you took the wrong mission.';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=11918 SET `male_text`='Oh yes, that\'s right.$B$BSo, here we are invading deep into the upper reaches of Blackrock Spire, against their lord and leader; this was before Drakkisath. Not too smart if you ask me, but our leader, Anthion Harmon, you met him, was always one who loved a challenge.$B$BSurprisingly, everything went according to plan, right up to the point where we were prying Valthalak\'s spellbook out of his stiff fingers. That\'s when it all went south.$B$BShould I continue? You look like your eyes are glazing over.', `female_text`='';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=11919 SET `male_text`='No, no, please continue... it\'s just that the air up here is so, um, smoky.', `female_text`='No, no, please continue... it\'s just that the air up here is so, um, smoky.';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=11920 SET `male_text`='<Bodley looks at you dubiously, but continues...>$B$BThere we are, spellbook in hand, and Kormok, our two-headed ogre necromancer, gets this strange look in all four of his eyes. It was really creepy, because that second set of eyes always kind of looked dead, like a cow\'s eyes, you know? So, all of a sudden he just reaches out and rips this amulet off that Valthalak was wearing.$B$BThe rest of the company went crazy; some of us telling them to leave it alone, and others who wanted it for themselves.', `female_text`='';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=11921 SET `male_text`='Please continue, Bodley.', `female_text`='Please continue, Bodley.';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=11922 SET `male_text`='Sheesh, you don\'t have to beg! Anyways, I\'m almost done with the story.$B$BSo, the whole company is in the middle of that massive chamber fighting over this amulet, and you know how it echoes in there! In the end it was broken into three pieces, and we rolled the dice, with it going to various people or groups.$B$BThe rest is a bit of a blur, though, because it was at about that time that old Valthalak\'s spirit decided to make an entrance and start summoning forth all of these spectral assassins.', `female_text`='';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=11923 SET `male_text`='I thought you were almost done?', `female_text`='I thought you were almost done?';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=11924 SET `male_text`='Cool your heels!$B$B<Bodley grumbles something under his breath about the impatience of the living>$B$BAs I was saying, Lord Valthalak\'s spirit and spectral assassins, summoned forth through his necromantic dabbling, started to assail us. Let me tell you, at that point we weren\'t in any condition to fight back, so we ran. I can still remember Mor Grayhoof, one of our druids, slip and fall at one point into the lower reaches of the spire.$B$BThe rest as they say, is history.', `female_text`='';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=11925 SET `male_text`='What happened to your mercenary company, The Veiled Blade?', `female_text`='What happened to your mercenary company, The Veiled Blade?';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=11926 SET `male_text`='We broke up afterward, that\'s what happened. Too much bad blood, I guess...it had been building for a while. And the thing with the amulet was the straw that broke the kodo\'s back.$B$BEver since then Valthalak\'s servants have been picking us off one by one. Most of the amulet piece holders are dead, their souls corrupted by the portion of Valthalak\'s spirit contained within it.$B$BThat\'s why I\'m glad that you\'re here, $n. With your help we\'ll be able to recombine the amulet and return it to Lord Valthalak!', `female_text`='';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=11927 SET `male_text`='Your meddling ends here, $n!  Lord Valthalak shall have his revenge!', `female_text`='Your meddling ends here, $n!  Lord Valthalak shall have his revenge!';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=11928 SET `male_text`='Friends of yours?', `female_text`='';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=11929 SET `male_text`='Use your tonk action bar above your standard action bar to attack other tonks.', `female_text`='';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=11930 SET `male_text`='', `female_text`='I\'ll be fine for now, don\'t worry about me.  I\'ll find a way out of here once I\'ve performed some cleansing rituals in this room.  Foul magic taints this place, $n.';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=11931 SET `male_text`='', `female_text`='You did it... you\'ve slain Baron Rivendare!  The Argent Dawn shall hear of your valiant deeds!';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=11932 SET `male_text`='Talk about making the wrong investment!$B$BLord Valthalak\'s dark book of spells fetched a pretty penny in the black market.  It\'s too bad he didn\'t take too kindly to getting his possessions stolen.  That stinker got us even after he\'d been dead for months!', `female_text`='';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=11933 SET `male_text`='Ysida lives thanks to your courage, $n.  I am deeply in your debt and shall assist you as much as it is in my power.', `female_text`='';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=11934 SET `male_text`='What are these Tonk Control Consoles?', `female_text`='What are these Tonk Control Consoles?';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=11935 SET `male_text`='', `female_text`='Our newest attraction, and at no cost to you I might add, these miniature tanks, or Tonks as we\'ve cleverly named them, can be controlled from any of the Tonk Control Consoles spread throughout the faire.$B$BAll that you have to do is activate an available control console. Each tonk will come equipped with a stock set of devices, and a random special power to unleash upon your enemy!$B$BHold epic battles with your friends, cruise around, or just cause wild mayhem... the choice is yours!';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=11936 SET `male_text`='Tell me about the cannon.', `female_text`='Tell me about the cannon.';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=11937 SET `male_text`='', `female_text`='The Blastenheimer 5000 Ultra Cannon is a state-of-the-art single person projectile device. Delivering its payload at near the speed of a dragon, the cannon is the pride and joy of the Blastenheimer family, world renown for their aeronautical and combustible feats!$B$BIf you\'d like to be launched through the skies to fly free as a bird, seek out Maxima Blastenheimer on the east end of the faire. I hear that she\'s placed a target ring way over on Crystal Lake for you to aim for as you sail through the air!';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=11938 SET `male_text`='', `female_text`='The Blastenheimer 5000 Ultra Cannon is a state-of-the-art single person projectile device. Delivering its payload at near the speed of a dragon, the cannon is the pride and joy of the Blastenheimer family, world renown for their aeronautical and combustible feats!$B$BIf you\'d like to be launched through the skies to fly free as a bird, seek out Maxima Blastenheimer on the south edge of Thunder Bluff\'s Hunter Rise. She\'ll aim you at the target far to south on Stonebull Lake!';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=11939 SET `male_text`='%s goes into a rage after seeing $n fall in battle!', `female_text`='%s goes into a rage after seeing $n fall in battle!';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=11940 SET `male_text`='', `female_text`='It is said that Kel\'Thuzad seeks the legendary Atiesh, greatstaff of the Guardian.$B$BYes, the very staff once held by Medivh.';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=11941 SET `male_text`='Watch your step, $r. We of the Brotherhood of the Light are not as lenient as our brethren when it comes to meting justice to those that would do this world wrong.$B$BWoe unto those that would anger Korfax.$B$BNow if you have no business with me or the other members of the Brotherhood, please leave so that we may continue our meeting. \n', `female_text`='';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=11942 SET `male_text`='The Lich King is attempting to make his presence known in our world. This must not be allowed to occur.\n', `female_text`='';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=11943 SET `male_text`='What is the Brotherhood of the Light? Well... We are all members of the Argent Dawn at the core - members of the Argent Dawn that aren\'t held in check by morals, guilt and useless human emotion. Consider us Scarlet Crusade minus the stupidity, lack of leadership, and blind zealotry.$B$BDon\'t let the Scarlet Commander tell you otherwise.$B$BAnd don\'t let Tyrosus know I said that... It would be a terrible shame if I had to brutally maim him should a brawl break out.\n', `female_text`='';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=11944 SET `male_text`='', `female_text`='The Argent Dawn might be impotent idealists but their delusional leader knows that they are outmatched. I have been sent here as an emissary of the Scarlet Crusade. An ambassador, if you will... It is doubtful that we could even dent the armies of Kel\'Thuzad - united or not - but we might be able to contain them long enough for some sort of miracle to happen.$B$BAs for me? I\'ll die in battle...$B$B<Marjhan shrugs.>\n';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=11945 SET `male_text`='', `female_text`='That is wonderous, Rimblat! Even this foul, sundered earth is not beyond healing.';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=11946 SET `male_text`='Watch, druid. The earth still breathes. It yearns to be cleansed.', `female_text`='';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=11947 SET `male_text`='The title is misleading. I\'m really a very nice person once you get to know me.', `female_text`='';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=11948 SET `male_text`='They almost sent my brother, Loksey, to this gathering. He cannot even take care of his hounds, let alone represent the Scarlet Crusade in a competent manner.', `female_text`='';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=11949 SET `male_text`='I\'ve been expec...$B$B<Rimblat coughs.>$B$BExcuse me, old habit. I am Rimblat of the Earthen Ring. ', `female_text`='';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=11950 SET `male_text`='', `female_text`='Hello, $c. Please excuse me as I am having a conversation with Rimblat. He believes that even this land is not beyond saving.';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=11951 SET `male_text`='What is it that you want, lemming? Get out of my sight before you find out why I am known as the Wrathcaster.', `female_text`='';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=11952 SET `male_text`='You want a fight?  A fight you\'ll get!', `female_text`='';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=11953 SET `male_text`='I\'m going to kick yer ugly head in!', `female_text`='';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=11954 SET `male_text`='I crush weaklings like you every day!  Bring it on!', `female_text`='';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=11955 SET `male_text`='Your insolence is appalling, fool!  I shall feast on your soul!', `female_text`='';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=11956 SET `male_text`='Who dares to disturb my eternal rest?  Your deaths will be slow and painful!', `female_text`='';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=11957 SET `male_text`='You\'re but worms beneath my feet.  You dare challenge me?', `female_text`='';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=11958 SET `male_text`='First Kormok crush your bones!  Then Kormok burn your soul!', `female_text`='';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=11959 SET `male_text`='You so little and puny... you no make good servants for Kormok!', `female_text`='';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=11960 SET `male_text`='What is Dreadnaught armor?', `female_text`='What is Dreadnaught armor?';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=11961 SET `male_text`='The first suit of Dreadnaught armor was made exclusively for the Scarlet Highlord Mograine.  Whilst donning the full suit, the Highlord looked himself to be a demon from the depths of the Nether.$B$BAye, \'twas quite a sight to behold as Mograine would wade into a hundred Scourge, Ashbringer held high, and come out on the other side in a cloud of dust and flames - enemies left in ashes beneath his feet.', `female_text`='';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=11962 SET `male_text`='Continue please.', `female_text`='Continue please.';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=11963 SET `male_text`='It was not until after his controversial death that the knights and warriors of Lordaeron would wear similarly fashioned suits in honor of their fallen hero. While the death of Mograine was a great victory for Kel\'Thuzad, the resulting martyrdom would be felt until the end of the war.$B$BWhere one did fall, many would rise...', `female_text`='';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=11964 SET `male_text`='Anything else?', `female_text`='Anything else?';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=11965 SET `male_text`='During your battles with the Scourge in Naxxramas, should you come across desecrated battlements and wartorn plate scraps, return them to me and I shall craft for you a piece of this armor worn by heroes.', `female_text`='';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=11966 SET `male_text`='All of Nature\'s might is at my disposal, puny mortals. Let us see which of my many forms it will be that ends your suffering!', `female_text`='';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=11967 SET `male_text`='Muahahahaha! What is this pathetic spectacle I see before me? Well, what are you waiting for? I hunger, and you look as if you may make for a passable appetizer!', `female_text`='';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=11968 SET `male_text`='You think you can summon us? We are the ones that summon, not you! We bash you good for this and suck the marrow from your bones!', `female_text`='';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=11969 SET `male_text`='I\'m what you call a capitalist, $r.', `female_text`='';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=11970 SET `male_text`='', `female_text`='In life, I focused my energies on healing others. Let us see in death how much pain I can cause!';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=11971 SET `male_text`='', `female_text`='Hello, brother.';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=11972 SET `male_text`='Hello, sister. What have we here?', `female_text`='';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=11973 SET `male_text`='', `female_text`='Would-be interlopers, I\'m afraid.';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=11974 SET `male_text`='Shall we slay them for the impertinence of disturbing our sleep?', `female_text`='';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=11975 SET `male_text`='', `female_text`='Yes, we shall!';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=11976 SET `male_text`='What is Redemption armor?', `female_text`='What is Redemption armor?';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=11977 SET `male_text`='The armor of Redemption was worn by our most pious knights - armor worthy of the Lightbringer himself!$B$BThousands fell in the last war; their vestments stripped from their corpses and taken to the dread citadel of Naxxramas.$B$BIt is said that the death knights of Naxxramas corrupt the Redemption plate mail for their own use.$B$BSuch tragedy... ', `female_text`='';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=11978 SET `male_text`='What is Cryptstalker armor?', `female_text`='What is Cryptstalker armor?';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=11979 SET `male_text`='The preternatural ability of the crypt fiend to hunt and kill its foe is one studied and vaunted by men in my profession. I, myself, have slain thousands of the beasts in my crusade to rid this world of Scourge.$B$BWhile I loathe the crypt fiend for its merciless nature, its abilities must be admired. It has a job and it does it - very well.', `female_text`='';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=11980 SET `male_text`='Continue please.', `female_text`='Continue please.';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=11981 SET `male_text`='I have discovered a use for the carapace of the crypt fiend and its various body parts. I am able to fashion an extremely light and very deadly set of armor by combining the fragments with some of the desecrated magical armors lost in Naxxramas.', `female_text`='';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=11982 SET `male_text`='I am unable to teach a Tauren to ride a Skeletal Mount.  I am sorry but there is nothing I can do for you.', `female_text`='I am unable to teach a Tauren to ride a Skeletal Mount.  I am sorry but there is nothing I can do for you.';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=11983 SET `male_text`='What brings a tauren to the Plaguelands?', `female_text`='What brings a tauren to the Plaguelands?';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=11984 SET `male_text`='In the last war, tauren fought. Shaman were sent in defense of this world against the Scourge invasion. Most lost their lives. Many were otherwise ripped asunder, their body parts used for foul experiments in that cursed citadel. I mourn their passing but my heart swells with pride at their courage.', `female_text`='';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=11985 SET `male_text`='Continue please.', `female_text`='Continue please.';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=11986 SET `male_text`='I was a young tauren, barely having reached adolescence at the time, but I knew that those that would brave the battles for our freedom were well protected in my namesake\'s vestments.', `female_text`='';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=11987 SET `male_text`='The name of Earthshatter has been one held by my family for hundreds of years. And like my father and his father before him, I too have inherited the right to create the vestments of my namesake. ', `female_text`='';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=12003 SET `male_text`='What is it that you do exactly, Rohan?', `female_text`='What is it that you do exactly, Rohan?';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=12004 SET `male_text`='Ah, as the title states I am an assassin for the Scarlet Crusade. I spend my days exterminating high priority targets and nights at the Gadgetzan discotheque. Dancing is my true calling. Assassination just pays the bills.', `female_text`='';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=12005 SET `male_text`='So what brings you to Light\'s Hope?', `female_text`='So what brings you to Light\'s Hope?';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=12006 SET `male_text`='Good question, $r. In my younger days I was footloose and fancy free without a care in the world. In those days I would sing in a barber shop quartet out of Stormwind known as the Four Dons. That\'s where I learned how to craft the Bonescythe digs.', `female_text`='';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=12007 SET `male_text`='What? Bonescythe?', `female_text`='What? Bonescythe?';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=12008 SET `male_text`='Yes, Bonescythe. You see, it was our tenor, an ornery fellow known as Don Julio, who got me started on the whole thing. In his travels throughout Lordaeron, Don Julio picked up many interesting skills, one of them being the ability to take the bones of fallen Scourge and fashion them into a lethal set of leather armor - perfectly suited for an assassin.', `female_text`='';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=12009 SET `male_text`='Wow, you\'re insane, aren\'t you?', `female_text`='Wow, you\'re insane, aren\'t you?';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=12010 SET `male_text`='I\'m as sane as the next guy, $g fella:lady;. Believe what you will, but I AM capable of fashioning this armor. If you\'re interested, maybe we can make a deal. The sooner I can get out of the assassination business, the better.', `female_text`='';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=12011 SET `male_text`='Hey wait, Gadgetzan has a disco?', `female_text`='Hey wait, Gadgetzan has a disco?';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=12012 SET `male_text`='Members only, scrub!\n', `female_text`='';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=12015 SET `male_text`='Hello, Rayne. What brings the Cenarion Circle to the Plaguelands?', `female_text`='Hello, Rayne. What brings the Cenarion Circle to the Plaguelands?';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=12016 SET `male_text`='', `female_text`='We are all drawn here for different reasons, $c.$B$B<Rayne smiles.>$B$BI am here to meet with Rimblat of the Earthen Ring. He has some interesting theories on cleansing these lands.';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=12017 SET `male_text`='Are these lands not beyond healing? They look pretty beat up.', `female_text`='Are these lands not beyond healing? They look pretty beat up.';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=12018 SET `male_text`='', `female_text`='I think not. Rimblat has already proven that new life can grow from the sundered earth. Now we must find a way to reproduce and, more importantly, sustain the growth.$B$BWhile I am here, I am also offering my services to adventurers entering Naxxramas.';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=12019 SET `male_text`='What kind of services?', `female_text`='What kind of services?';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=12020 SET `male_text`='', `female_text`='I am a crafter of some renown, $c. With the proper materials, I am able to craft an armor known as Dreamwalker. Druids - and even some shaman - are drawn to this armor due to its magical properties. Are you interested?';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=12021 SET `male_text`='What is Atiesh?\n', `female_text`='What is Atiesh?\n';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=12022 SET `male_text`='', `female_text`='Like Kel\'Thuzad, I too was once a mage of the Kirin Tor. And like Kel\'Thuzad, I seek the legendary Atiesh, greatstaff of the Guardian. Our fates are intertwined as such, $c.';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=12023 SET `male_text`='What Guardian? I don\'t understand any of this.', `female_text`='What Guardian? I don\'t understand any of this.';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=12024 SET `male_text`='', `female_text`='Progeny of Aegwynn, he that would be the last Guardian of Tirisfal... Medivh.';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=12025 SET `male_text`='Please continue.', `female_text`='Please continue.';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=12026 SET `male_text`='', `female_text`='It is a story of legend and one that I do not have the time nor the inclination to retell. Just know that Medivh was the last of the Guardians. The greatstaff of Atiesh was a focal point of his power and a focal point of corruption.';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=12027 SET `male_text`='What corruption?', `female_text`='What corruption?';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=12028 SET `male_text`='', `female_text`='The corruption of a fallen titan. The corruption of the Destroyer. After all, the staff was forged from the seed of hate. That is, of course, what has brought me here...';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=12029 SET `male_text`='Please continue.', `female_text`='Please continue.';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=12030 SET `male_text`='', `female_text`='After the fall of Karazhan, the Kirin Tor dispatched an assembly of mages to search the tower and seize all items of import... for the purposes of \"research.\" It was then that the fabled staff was discovered and brought back to Dalaran.';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=12031 SET `male_text`='Please continue.', `female_text`='Please continue.';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=12032 SET `male_text`='', `female_text`='What followed were a series of tragic events, leading to the death of every Kirin Tor mage that came into contact with Atiesh.$B$BYou see, it was an artifact with sentience. A sentience granted to it by Sargeras...';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=12033 SET `male_text`='What?', `female_text`='What?';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=12034 SET `male_text`='', `female_text`='<Angela nods.>$B$BAfter the deaths, the Six decided that the best course of action was to seal the staff behind impenetrable barriers of magic and appoint a watcher: A guardian of the staff... I would be that watcher.';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=12035 SET `male_text`='This is disturbing. Please continue.', `female_text`='This is disturbing. Please continue.';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=12036 SET `male_text`='', `female_text`='There is not much more to tell. Dalaran was nearly wholly destroyed by Archimonde, the staff lost, presumably shattered by the barrier\'s fail-safe mechanisms.$B$BThere are those that believe the staff to be the cause of Archimonde\'s reprisal.';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=12037 SET `male_text`='Please, tell me more.', `female_text`='Please, tell me more.';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=12038 SET `male_text`='', `female_text`='After the fall of Dalaran, I took my leave from the Kirin Tor. I spent years watching over Atiesh, only to have my purpose amongst the Kirin Tor taken from me in one fell swoop. I would find the staff, though it might take a lifetime. That is how I came to join the Argent Dawn and why I am here now.';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=12039 SET `male_text`='Is there anything else?', `female_text`='Is there anything else?';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=12040 SET `male_text`='', `female_text`='I have tracked the various fragments of the staff across this world and in doing so, discovered Kel\'Thuzad\'s plans to reform the staff. He has already collected several of the staff\'s fragments - which are being held by his most trusted lieutenants.$B$BI cannot emphasize enough the importance of keeping the greatstaff of the Guardian out of Kel\'Thuzad\'s grasp. Frankly, I do not know what the result would be, other than a catastrophe of epic proportion.';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=12041 SET `male_text`='What is Plagueheart armor?', `female_text`='What is Plagueheart armor?';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=12042 SET `male_text`='It is power, imbecile.$B$B<Mataus\'s eyes darken.>$B$BThese fools send idiots like you into Naxxramas to retrieve desecrated armor so that they may purify it and restore the pieces to their former glory.$B$B<Mataus spits.>$B$BJust the thought of such utter stupidity brings the bile up to my throat.$B$BI too seek that armor, but in its most foul and desecrated form.', `female_text`='';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=12043 SET `male_text`='I also seek such power.', `female_text`='I also seek such power.';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=12044 SET `male_text`='I make no pretenses, maggot. The darkness such items hold could very well destroy the both of us. That is why the price is so high. If I\'m going to die, it\'s going to be as a rich man.$B$BAnd I don\'t give an ounce of gnoll spit how you die, only that you do as I ask. Bring me what I require and we will both benefit - or die, but I\'ve already explained this...', `female_text`='';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=12045 SET `male_text`='Tell me about faith, Father.', `female_text`='Tell me about faith, Father.';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=12046 SET `male_text`='Faith... Some have lost it, others have found it. It cannot be destroyed and it cannot be created.$B$BOr perhaps you speak of the vestments of Faith? Armor worn by our priests and most devout warriors into battle against the Scourge during the last war.$B$BAye, much of it is lost... Stolen by the fiends of Naxxramas.', `female_text`='';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=12047 SET `male_text`='', `female_text`='Your message did reach us, Commander, but by no means is our involvement here sanctioned by the Grand Crusader.';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=12048 SET `male_text`='Your leader takes residence at the doorstep to Naxxramas. Do you think he does not feel the pressure?\n', `female_text`='';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=12049 SET `male_text`='%s lowers the sound of his voice to a whisper.', `female_text`='';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=12050 SET `male_text`='Even demons are capable of fear...', `female_text`='';
UPDATE `broadcast_text` WHERE `entry`=12051 SET `male_text`='Scourge activity in the Plaguelands has increased ten-fold. We are receiving reports of Scourge attacks from as far away as Kalimdor! Now how do you suppose this has happened? How have the wretched undead done that which was previously thought impossible? Is nowhere safe?', `female_text`='';
